  "Phil has asked for a status of this work.  John Keller and I and a couple of others will be meeting with Phil on Thursday, May 24 and review the information below.   "Subject": "San Juan Lateral MAOP Upgrade",
  "To": "l..johnson@enron.com, steven.harris@enron.com, shelley.corman@enron.com,",

  "Date": "Fri, 4 Jan 2002 13:12:35 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 2": "00 - 3:00 p.m., the Corporate server team will split the sysAdmiral Fault Tolerance Databases and Master Services on \t\t\t\tNAHOU-BPMS01P and NAHOU-BPMSFT01P. The NAHOU-BPMS01P Database/Master will be used for Estate Scheduling needs and \t\t\tNAHOU-BPMSFT01P will be used for Netco Scheduling Needs. The servers may have to be rebooted during this change but no impact to the \t\tsysAdmiral application is expected.  After the environments are split there will be no more replication between the two servers or Fault Jan. \t\tTolerance.",
  "From 3": "00 - 4:00 p.m., the Win2000 team will decommission DFS Server NAHOUTRD to replace existing the DFS NAHOU cluster marked for \t\tNetco.  No impact to ETS users is expected.",
  "From 6": "00 - 6:30 p.m., the Corporate server team will move cluster notes nahou-us06 and nahou-us07.  These two nodes will be evicted out of \t\tthere respective clusters and recreated as an application cluster.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 7": "00 a.m. through 1/11 at 5:00 p.m., Facilities will perform the annual maintenance on the rooftop chillers.  The chillers will be taken \t\tdown one at a time during the maintenance.  No impact to ETS is expected.",

No impact to ETS users is expected.",
  "From 12": "00 p.m. through 1/15 at 12:00 p.m., the SAP team will move the XMS database from Seattle to Denver.  During this maintenance, the web-based XMS (employee expense) system will be unavailable.",

Some of the applications affected by this outage include: Corporate-wide applications accessing the Envision web query, FileNet Panagon IDM Desktop, FileNet  IDM for R3, Panagon Capture professional.   "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "KOMP Horticultural - Sale of Leased Plants",
  "The KOMP Horticultural contract for the maintenance of leased floor plants has been cancelled.  Plant maintenance is not being performed on the leased plants in the Enron Building on floors 3 through 49.  Rather than removing the plants from the building, KOMP Horticultural has chosen to offer the plants to Enron employees for sale.  On January 16th from 11": "00 AM to 2:00 PM, KOMP will have a table on the south side of the plaza, by the up escalator, for those employees interested in purchasing a plant. At the time of purchase, KOMP will give a special sticker to place on the container of the sold plant (do not bring plants to the plaza for purchase).  Plants will not be allowed to be removed from the building unless they have the KOMP sold sticker on the container.",
  "The following guidelines must be followed": "",
  "To": "dl-ga-all_enron_houston@enron.com",

  "Along with any comments we may have on the \"Ideas\" document itself, FERC Staff distributed a set of three questions for consideration and/or comment from industry and the public.  The questions follow  -- note that Staff is particularly eager to collect positive anecdotes on how these ideas are already working on projects": "",
  "Bcc": "janet.butler@enron.com, karina.prizont@enron.com",
  "Cc": "janet.butler@enron.com, karina.prizont@enron.com",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Sun, 28 Oct 2001 14:01:01 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "nancy.bagot@enron.com",
  "Link to \"Ideas\" document": "http://www.ferc.gov/gas/stakeholder.pdf",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c3639156.1075858834364.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Part 1": "Are we on target?  [Please let us know of any additions, omissions, or editorial changes you recommend for \"Ideas for Better Stakeholder Involvement...\"]",
  "Part 2": "Ideas for implementation  [Please give us your good ideas about how to put the ideas discussed here today to work.  This can be for projects you are involved with or for other projects of which you are aware.]",
  "Part 3": "Examples of successful implementation [Please describe examples of how using these concepts helped make your experience or involvement with a project better.]",
  "Subject": "Briefing on FERC OEP Facility-Planning Outreach",
  "The Gas Outreach Team (Rich Hoffmann, Lauren O'Donnell, Jeff Shenot, Howard Wheeler) presented their findings of Action Options for the four major stakeholder sectors": "Pipeline Industry, Agency (local, state and resource agencies), Citizen and FERC Staff.  There is a slide presentation that should be made available online soon.",
  "Though FERC's Office of Energy Projects intends to hold more public and industry outreach seminars, this sixth seminar was the last of this series; OEP presented their final draft of \"Ideas for Better Stakeholder Involvement in the Interstate Natural Gas Pipeline Planning Pre-Filing Process": "Industry, Agencies, Citizens and FERC Staff.\"",

{
  "10/26/2001 05": "08 PM EDT",
  "15": "16 EDT OCTOBER 26, 2001",
  "2001-10-26 15": "36 (New York)",
  "2001-10-26 16": "18 (New York)",
  "2001-10-26 17": "14 (New York)",
  "But what does Enron do now? It's very simple. Come clean, clean up the mess and refocus on its core business": "wholesale energy markets, risk management and retail energy services. They support each other and create a platform that can be plenty profitable without a lot of gimmicks.",
  "By Christopher Edmonds \u003cmailto": "cedmonds@thestreet.com\u003e",
  "By Peter Eavis \u003cmailto": "peavis@thestreet.com\u003e",
  "CONTACT": "Keller Rohrback L.L.P. Liza Catabay, 800/776-6044 investor@kellerrohrback.com www.SeattleClassAction.com",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=ANSI_X3.4-1968",
  "Date": "Fri, 26 Oct 2001 14:45:48 -0700 (PDT)",
  "Dealings with a related party have tarnished Enron's (ENE": "NYSE - news - commentary) reputation and crushed its stock, but it looks like that case is far from unique.",
  "From": "m..schmidt@enron.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c11808437.1075858834687.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Source": "Detox",
  "Subject": "Enron Mentions",
  "The rumors -- from a pending bankruptcy to a Justice Department investigation -- are, for now, just that. And, Enron did not single-handedly cause the California power crisis, nor is Royal Dutch/Shell (RD": "NYSE - news - commentary) about to make a bid to buy the company. Sources do tell me that head-count reductions are likely through employee buyout offers and the company is set to refocus on its core energy business. And, while former CEO Jeff Skilling shares culpability for the current mess, his departure appears only indirectly related to Enron's current woes.",
  "This week, a number of energy market players reduced exposure to Enron. However, in a Friday press release, CEO Lay said that Enron was the \"market-maker of choice in wholesale gas and power markets.\" He added": "\"It is evident that our customers view Enron as the major liquidity source of the global energy markets.\"",
  "URL": "\u003chttp://www.thestreet.com/comment/chrisedmonds/10003075.html\u003e",
  "Under The Radar": "Enron's Flickering Bulb",
  "Under the Radar": "Enron's Flickering Bulb",
  "While the bulb at Enron (ENE": "NYSE - news - commentary) may not have burnt out, it's clearly flickering. To date, investors aren't sure whether Chairman and CEO Ken Lay is up to the task of re-energizing the company he once built to greatness.",

  "X-Origin": "Corman-S",
  "X-To": "",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": ""

  "At 5": "00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will remove access to CORPHOU-DC07 (172.23.226.23, primary/secondary DNS) and NAHOU-NSWN03 (172.23.226.24, primary/secondary WINS) from devices within ECN.   All servers/workstations/equipment using these for WINS/DNS must have their settings changed. Use 172.16.7.120 for DNS and 172.16.7.116 for WINS in their place by this 5/01.",
  "Beginning today through 3/19, the Corporate Security team will replace the GRC.dat file in W": "\\scripts\\UpdateGRC and W:\\scripts\\logon\\Win2000\\original to point NAV clients on nahou-apnav01 to nahou-apnav02 (only about 650 left).  No impact is expected.",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Thu, 14 Mar 2002 13:44:05 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 10": "00 - 11:00 p.m., Telephony Services will perform the monthly maintenance on the CMS (Call management) systems.  This maintenance affects only call center reporting.  No impact to users is expected.",
  "From 11": "00 - 11:15 a.m., the Corporate Security group will remove the svceu_SAPConnect account from CORP Domain Admins group.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 2": "00 - 4:00 p.m., the Blackberry Network Team will perform maintenance on a component of the Blackberry Network.  Some customers may experience delays in receiving messages.  It is also possible that messages sent from he Blackberry may be returned.  Returned messages can be resent after the maintenance is complete.",
  "From 4": "00 - 6:00 p.m.., the Unix Team will upgrade the Time server.  Timex.ect.enron.com which is now on a Unix desktop network will be moved to a production network and to Netra T1 hardware. It would be doing the same activity as Rolex which was replaced on Monday. All clients are now pointing to new Rolex server \u0026 Timex.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 5": "00 - 6:00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will change the DHCP scopes to update the secondary WINS and DNS entries.  This change will affect workstations that get their IP addresses via DHCP.  All scopes are renewed on a 24-hour basis so all changes should be completed by 3/19.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 8": "00 p.m. through 3/17 at 6:00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will re-enable the File Replication Service on all Corporate domain controllers.  This change is necessary to replicate security policies.   FRS will be started on Corp DCs one at a time, watching to be sure replication completes.  Brief outages of Corp.enron.com security policies and possibly Exchange may occur.  The Messaging team will be notified if replication causes problems.  Support staff whose applications experience problems due to FRS should contact the solution center at ext. 54745.",

  "At 10": "30 pm on Saturday night, Mark Cowley from the server team will contact the HotTap Helpdesk to get approval to start the maintenance window.  The maintenance window will not begin until all processing for the pipelines is complete.  If we have any problems or issues he will contact me and I will start the escalation process.",

  "Subject": "Maintenance Window-Saturday, Oct 27",
  "This Saturday night,  October 27, starting at 10": "30 pm fiber maintenance will be performed in the wiring closet on EB41.  During this maintenance window the jacket that covers and protects the fiber will be pulled back tight and secured.  This fiber connects the 41st floor wiring closet with the server room on 41, where the TMS servers are located.   While we do not expect this maintenance to have any impact, if we do have any issues with the fiber it can be replaced within an estimated 2 hour window.  Outage impact would then be lose of connectivity with the Enron LAN from that server room, therefore TMS would be unavailable.",

  "Please note": "Online booking mileage bonus does not apply to E-Savers.",
  "Purchase these land packages online at http": "//www.usairwaysvacations.com/pricing_res.htm  Simply enter your origin and destination cities, departure date, number of adults, children's ages and click \"Search For Vacation.\"  Choose \"Hotel and Car Vacations for 1-59 nights,\" confirm your departure date and indicate the number of nights for your vacation.   "Subject": "MISO-PJM-SPP Single Market Forum on 2/8/02 will be broadcast by the",
  "The Capitol Connection is pleased to announce that it will broadcast (via the internet and telephone only) the Single Market Design Forum convened by the Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator, Inc. (MISO), PJM Interconnection and Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP).  It will be held on Friday, February 8, 2002 from 9 am to 1 pm ET.  For more information on this Forum please go to": "",
  "This Forum will be available to Capitol Connection FERC Annual Internet Contract Patrons at no additional charge.  If you do not have a yearly Internet contract, and would like to receive the Forum via the Internet or phone, click here \u003chttp": "//www.capitolconnection.gmu.edu/file:///S:/webshare/capcon/Special%20Meeting-Half%20Day.htm\u003e for the contract or call 703.993.3100:",
  "X-FileName": "scorman (Non-Privileged).pst",
  "X-Folder": "\\Shelley_Corman_Mar2002\\Corman, Shelley\\Inbox\\Archives\\Old Messages",
  "X-From": "Capitol Connection \u003ccapcon@gmu.edu\u003e",
  "X-Origin": "Corman-S",
  "X-To": "",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": "",
  "www.miso-pjm-spp.com \u003chttp": "//www.miso-pjm-spp.com/\u003eThis Forum is to discuss the development of a single market that meets the needs of all customers and stakeholders using the electric power grid in the regions served by them.  Central to the development of a single market is a design that meets the needs of market participants through one-stop shopping."
}

  "Join this outstanding group of speakers at the only conference that gives electric power executives the chance to benchmark their security procedures with peers and experts.   "Message-ID": "\u003c26749109.1075861097165.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Power industry executives will examine the impact of heightened security measures on their companies' day-to-day operations.  Crucial factors that will be discussed include strengthening data security and protecting against cybercrime. Hear about Security measures that these industry leaders are adopting": "Utilicorp United, Inc., Rochester Gas \u0026 Electric Corporation, PEPCO, National Regulatory Research Institute, National Association of Regulated Utility Commissioners, Electric Power Research Institute and many more.",
  "Representative Jeff Morris of the Washington State Legislature and Chair of the House Telecommunications, Technology and Energy Committee will keynote at CBI's Safety and Security in the Electric Power Industry. http": "//www.cbinet.com/events/PB231/index.html  The Federal Bureau of Investigation will discuss how Houston's National Infrastructure Protection Center benefits the energy industry.",

  "From": "grs4ferc@starpower.net",

  "REQUEST A COPY": "grs4ferc@starpower.net \u003cmailto:grs4ferc@starpower.net\u003e or call 202-210-4771.",
  "Send suggestions on how the GRS' FERCwatch can better serve the energy community to grs4ferc@starpower.net \u003cmailto": "grs4ferc@starpower.net\u003e.",
  "Subject": "GRS' FERCwatch - 02/12/02",
  "The FERCwatch subscription list is used for the sole purpose of providing information on FERC and energy industry activity and will not be sold or otherwise distributed to any other business or organization.  For additions or removal from the FERCwatch notification list, please reply to grs4ferc@starpower.net \u003cmailto": "grs4ferc@starpower.net\u003e.",
  "The following items have been stricken from the Commission's open meeting agenda for February 13, 2002": "",
  "To request an order form and/or list of commenters please reply to grs4ferc@starpower.net \u003cmailto": "grs4ferc@starpower.net\u003e or call 202-210-4771.",

  "\"I came to writing fiction late, clumsily, and by a process that still remains a bit mysterious even to me,\" says Andrea Barrett, whose fiction speaks volumes about the ways in which we discover our true passions -- and what it means for Barrett to have found her own. Her latest, Servants of the Map, reveals profound connections between a number of characters who made appearances in her earlier books, Ship Fever and The Voyage of the Narwhal, and is highly recommended reading. We had a chance to talk with Andrea Barrett via email about her writing, her characters, and her latest work, in our exclusive Q\u0026A \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIJ0Am\u003e.",
  "\"In a lot of ways, writing is a way for me to see other places in the world that I can't physically go to,\" says Anthony Doerr, whose debut collection, The Shell Collector, takes his readers from Tanzania to the American West, from Africa to New England. At 28, Doerr has already visited parts of the world many of us may only know through reading. And in his remarkable debut collection of stories, a selection of the 2002 Barnes \u0026 Noble Discover Great New Writers program, we see what truths there are to be learned when one has spent time as a stranger in a strange land. Find out more in our exclusive interview \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIK0An\u003e.",
  "\"It's All About the Madeleines,\" by Anne Ursu \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0GNW0A6\u003e",
  "\"My novel, Spilling Clarence, is about memory -- or rather it's about remembering, which, I've come to believe, is a different kettle of fish,\" writes Anne Ursu in our exclusive essay. A selection of the 2002 Barnes \u0026 Noble Discover Great New Writers program, Spilling Clarence asks probing questions about the nature of memory -- and why we choose to forget. Read on to find out more about the origins of this very original debut, in \"It's All About the Madeleines \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0GNW0A6\u003e.\"",
  "\"Nobody today comes close to Twain,\" says Geoffrey C. Ward, author of Mark Twain, the companion biography to the Ken Burns documentary film that appeared on PBS in January. Perhaps no author in American history has achieved the international recognition of Mark Twain -- both as a writer and celebrity. Ward, who has collaborated with Burns on legendary projects such as Jazz and The Civil War, now presents us with a wise portrait of a writer whose inimitable wit and insight into the human condition have stood the test of time. In our exclusive Q\u0026A, we asked Geoffrey C. Ward a few questions \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0HHX0A2\u003e about his work with Ken Burns, and about the public and private persona of Samuel Langhorne Clemens, a.k.a. Mark Twain.",

  "If you no longer wish to receive email from Readers' Advantage (including special offers) please click here \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/profile?y=eFVU0EUb180BvfU\u003e.",
  "Let's be honest, we love chocolate and use every holiday possible as a reason to give and gladly receive the delectable indulgence. But more than any other holiday, Valentine's Day is a great time to give chocolate - not only because of its sweet connotations, but also because of chocolate's historical association with romance. Don't miss our recommendations for some great books to sweeten the gift \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FpW0Ae\u003e! And, thanks to our friends at Godiva, read more about the food that has been linked to love for more than 2000 years.",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c24481807.1075861088621.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Michael J. Fox's much-awaited memoir is due April 4th, but it's not the only big book we're looking forward to in the coming months -- Fran Drescher and Bobby Knight will also be telling their stories. Plus, a new Spenser mystery from Robert B. Parker is on the way, Ian McEwan's Atonement will soon be crossing the waters, and Jean M. Auel's Shelters of Stone is less than an Ice Age away. These and more are all available for preorder now \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIL0Ao\u003e.",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Neate Wins Whitbread, Library of Congress Preserves Its Pages, Rowling Says \"I Do,\" and Melvillians \"Call Me Ishmael\"  \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIM0Ap\u003e",
  "Neate Wins Whitbread, Library of Congress Preserves Its Pages, Rowling Says \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIM0Ap\u003e\t   \u003chttp://www.readersadvantage.com/newsletter/images/dot_clear.gif\u003e\tInside the Book Business",
  "Our Fiction Buyer Makes Her Selections \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIN0Aq\u003e",
  "Patrick Neate takes the 2001 Whitbread Award, the Library of Congress takes steps to preserve its collection, J. K. Rowling gets married in Scotland, and Melvillians celebrate Moby-Dick in a 25-hour marathon reading. All this -- plus a look at the shortlist for the 2001 Barnes \u0026 Noble Discover Great New Writers Award -- in another look inside the book business \u003chttp": "//email.bn.com/cgi-bin6/flo?y=hFVU0EUb180Bvf0FIM0Ap\u003e.",
  "Readers' Advantage \u003chttp": "//www.readersadvantage.com/newsletter/images/ntitle_ra-knowothersbox.gif\u003e",
  "Subject": "February News from Readers' Advantage",
  "There is more great content in our Archives, so you don't miss out on past exclusive features, interviews, and Q\u0026A's, including": "",
  "This is one of our favorite times of the year. With the holiday rush behind us, and the spring still several chilly weeks away, February is a wonderful month to settle down indoors with all those books you've had on your reading list. In this issue of the Readers' Advantage Newsletter, enrich your reading with a closer look at some authors you know, and an introduction to some we think you should know about. And don't forget to look in our Great Reads section, where our fiction buyer, Sessalee Hensley, has made her choice of great fiction titles out this month. You'll find all this and more -- enough to make you almost wish February would last longer -- so cozy up and enjoy this month of reading.\t   \u003chttp": "//www.readersadvantage.com/newsletter/images/dot_clear.gif\u003e",
  "To": "scorman@enron.com",
  "Whether it's a new collection of short stories by old favorites or a debut novel we highly recommend, February offers a wide assortment of fiction for all readers.   "E-SAVERS FARE REQUIREMENTS": "Fares do not include a $3 federal excise tax which will be imposed on each flight segment of your itinerary.  A flight segment is defined as a takeoff and a landing.   "4.\tI just received a call at 5": "15 PM from Rich Plachy at CS 17.  The station is on line with a 160 psig differential and vibration levels are much lower than this morning.  They are the highest at the end of the cooler.  When the station was shut down this morning because of the excessive vibrations, the differential was at 150 psig.  I believe that the removal of the blowdown valves at the end of the headers contributed to the vibration reduction.    I also believe that the support piers under the two headers are not sufficient and that another pier needs to be installed at the end of each cooler header.  We still intend to travel to CS 17 to collect pulsation data.",

  "Date": "Sat, 9 Feb 2002 11:02:02 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "cormanerb@cs.com",
  "I made it to Singapore at 1": "00 am on Sunday morning.  That should be 1:00 pm Saturday afternoon.  I had forgotten how long that flight is and there is no way I'd do it in coach/economy.  I'm currently in the Singapore Airlines Lounge, which has free internet access!  Imagine that, especially after our experience in Moscow.  I've taken a shower and changed clothes, but can not shave as my razor is in my checked luggage.  I have an 8:00 am flight for Jakarta.  Jakarta should be 13 hours ahead of Houston time.  I'll send an email Monday, from the office, advising you of my contact info.  You can send emails to me at my work email address.  I'll check them every morning at the office.",

  "fyi": "One of Joe's twin grandchildren (I believe the twins were born around September or October) is currently in the hospital (about the 4th day).  Ashley is the baby who has had some breathing difficulty from time to time.  She has had a viral infection and due to the shallow breathing, the doctor is keeping her in the hospital.   "Shelley--If you have time on your schedule, would you also attend this meeting.   "Subject": "GISB Board \u0026 EC Meeting Attendance",
  "The 2002 meeting schedule has not been finalized (neither dates nor locations).  In the past, all Board meetings and most EC meetings have been held in Houston.  For NAESB, this will change.  For 2002, none of the Board meetings will be in Houston and possibly none of the EC meetings will be in Houston.  Starting in June the EC meetings will probably move to two-day meetings (as they were in the past) because more than one quadrant may be in attendance.  New standards will be brought before the EC for vote.  New quadrants will probably have a flurry of new standards -- hopefully not to the extent we had at the beginning of GISB.  Below is the meeting schedule as I know it thus far": "",

  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Wed, 20 Feb 2002 12:30:06 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "theresa.hess@enron.com",
  "Last December the EC adopted revisions to standards based on the recommendations in the Sandia Labs Report.  These revisions have been incorporated into GISB's response document, which has been distributed to the EC.  This response document was received earlier this week; I have not verified GISB's work.  This item is not on the EC agenda, so I don't know the specific intent.  They may want the EC to approve the final version -- which means approving GISB's work.  I have a concern with that type of vote.  They may want the EC to approve the 'Executive Summary' and 'Conclusion' (total 3 pages).  I have no problem with that vote except that these documents have not been updated since the December revisions were made and are no longer correct.  I'll take care of during the EC meeting.  (NOTE": "The revisions to standards have not been distributed for ratification.)",

{
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Fri, 8 Feb 2002 13:48:39 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 10": "30 - 11:30 p.m., the Omaha Infrastructure team will reconfigure the power connections for the Omaha Inverse MUX.  This change will result in a total disruption of IP communication between Omaha and Houston.  The outage should only last for a few minutes.  The maintenance time will be coordinated with the HotTap helpdesk to ensure processing has been completed.  All support staff whose applications are affected by this outage should communicate this change to their customers.  Please ensure they are aware of the possibility of an extended outage in the event the Inverse MUX does not properly re-establish communications.  LAT and DecNet communications for gas control will not be affected by this maintenance.",
  "From 5": "00 p.m. - 6:00 a.m., the Envision team will perform hardware maintenance on the Envision system.  This outage will affect corporate-wide applications accessing the Envision web query, FileNet Panagon IDM Desktop, FileNet IDM for R3, Panagon Capture professional. Users will be able to access IBuyit and IPayit from SAP but will not be able to view invoices.",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c8844211.1075861086855.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",

  "SHelley": "I feel AWFULLLL!!! What can I do? YOu are just about the best friend I have ever had in my whole life and I feel like I am absolutely falling short on supporting you right now. Anyway... I am glad that you are going on the trip; My mom and dad said that they are going to pray for you every day (they go to Mass now everyday at St. Joseph's Villa in Philly) - same with my sisters -- they have all been asking about you. Lunch really was great and was definitely needed by me!
